      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see why setting $HOME is necessary here. It should be getting passed automatically from the environment, right?\n\nIs this code called during an emerge, because that would explain it. Every ebuild sets $HOME to a directory inside its work area. This would make the go cache useless since there would be a new one for every emerge and it would get wiped after the emerge is done.\n\nMaybe you should set $GOCACHE to explicitly point to a directory to use for the build cache.",
      "revId": "4493c8196d28d695a1afbbaf49c01f613a854514",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
